    "content": "Steve Krug — consent confirmed.\n\nThe implementation matches the proposal exactly. Two things I particularly appreciate:\n\n1. **The TEAM_AGREEMENTS.md update addresses my suggestion.** Adding the \"skipped CI = implicitly green\" clarification to step 11 removes ambiguity from the workflow. The team won't have to think about whether they need to wait when only docs changed. Good.\n\n2. **The \"what is NOT ignored\" list is a smart inclusion in the review.** It makes it easy to verify nothing important was accidentally excluded. All code paths (`src/`, `tests/`, `templates/`, `static/`, `migrations/`, etc.) still trigger CI as expected.\n\nNo blocking concerns. 9/9 consent from me."
